<p>
  That's added the form, but now we have two buttons, a "Submit" button and a "Save changes button". We probably want to replace the "Submit" button with the "Save changes button". So let's go ahead and do that. Copy and paste <code>&lt;%= f.submit 'Submit', class: 'btn btn-primary' %&gt;</code> and replace <code>&lt;button type="button" class="btn btn-primary">Save changes&lt;/button&gt;</code>. But now the submit button is outside the form. This will probably give us an error, so we need to make sure that the button is still in the form. We cna do his by moving where the form starts and where it ends like below:
